   <indicator ascending="0" measure="1">
    <title>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">Output Indicator</narrative>
    </title>
    <description>
     <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Availability of upgraded and improved Municipal Development Index to address the gender specific needs
2. Number of prepared Policy recommendations for integrating the MDI into local and regional development policy 
3. Number of priority areas/services identified  to be supported through Municipal Development Index 
4. Number of Digital solutions adopted in municipalities participating in at least three IMC partnerships to address the COVID-19 pandemic and improve local service delivery</narrative>
    </description>
    <baseline year="2021">
     <comment>
      <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Some data available
2. There is no Municipal Development Index integrated into local and regional development policy
3. There is no priority areas/services identified  to be supported through Municipal Development Index 
4. There are no Municipal Development Index partnerships to address the COVID-19 pandemic and improve local service delivery</narrative>
     </comment>
    </baseline>
    <period>
     <period-start iso-date="2021-01-01"></period-start>
     <period-end iso-date="2021-12-31"></period-end>
     <target>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Previously collected data verified and remedial actions identified; MDI methodology revised &amp; updated; data base sources with sex disaggregated data identified; MDI upgraded with gender sensitive, environmental and economic sensitive indicators ; Municipalities trained to use database sources/collect data according to updated MDI methodology and Manual for data collection &amp;analysis of the MDI ; Municipalities trained to use MDI indicators for mainstreaming gender equality in decision making processes on local level; 
2. National and municipal stakeholders that will serve as a core &#x201C;local and regional development policy group&#x201D; identified; Policy debates organized to discuss the importance/reusability of MDI data and use of MDI in support to local and regional development; Policy discussions organized to discuss setting up suitable legal instrument for regular data collection ; Legal instrument for regular data collection from municipalities identified and recommended; Policy debates organized to discuss the legal framework for integrating the MDI into local and regional development policy
3. Services to be supported identified based on findings from the Socio-Economic Impact Assessment, Integral Assessment on Municipal Crisis Management Response to COVID-19, and UN Women Mapping Study; Criteria for selection &amp; evaluation of IMC Proposals defined &amp; communicated with stakeholders; public call announced; IMC Projects selected and training on IMC for municipal officials/administration in selected municipalities delivered; Operationalization of the selected IMCs and implementation of IMC projects; 
4. Priority municipal services to be digitalized are identified and municipal IT capacities are assessed; Most appropriate digital solutions that are gender sensitive and reflect the needs of the most vulnerable communities identified and designed.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </target>
     <actual>
      <comment>
       <narrative xml:lang="EN">1.	MDI ranking for 2020 produced based on the data collected from 46 municipalities. The MDI methodology was revised and updated. Data base source with sex disaggregated data was identified and integrated in the MDI. MDI was upgraded with gender sensitive, environmental and economic sensitive indicators.
2.	The stakeholders important for MDI for production, collection or analysis of data were identified. Meetings with stakeholders and the experts were organized to promote the MDI (Statistical office, Ministry of Information Society and administration, Ministry of labor, Ministry of environment, Ministry of culture). 2 workshops organized with experts and representatives from Ministry of local self-government to discuss the integration of MDI indicators with the local and regional development policy. The services to be supported and key topics for the municipalities were identified and adequately presented in the Public call for projects.
3.	The services to be supported and key topics for the municipalities were identified and adequately presented in the Public call for projects. Criteria for selection and evaluation of Inter-municipal cooperation were defined and discussed with the main stakeholders: Bureau for regional development, Ministry of local self-government and the Association of municipalities (ZELS). Public call for project was launched and promoted on various websites. 8 info-sessions were organized in different regions. 105 persons from 47 municipalities (Mayors and administrative staff) from municipalities participated on the info-sessions. 16 projects received for funding and evaluated. Public information on the evaluation process published. 7 projects selected for implementation. 25 municipalities in total participating in the 7 selected projects for implementation. 3 trainings organized for 50 representatives from the selected municipalities. 
4.	3 projects supported on the topic of digitalization of municipal services. 1 IT expert engaged for assessment of municipal IT capacities and identification of priority municipal services. Individual meetings with municipalities have taken place for identification of priority services. The most appropriate digital solutions to respond to the needs of the most vulnerable communities are currently identified by the IT expert and the municipalities within the 3 selected projects.</narrative>
      </comment>
     </actual>
